Package com.github.ds67.jminicache.impl.storage

Interface StorageManagerIF<Key,​Value,​Wrapper>

  • Type Parameters:
    Key - Type of the key to access the cached items
    Value - Type of the cached item
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleCacheManager, SoftManager
    public interface StorageManagerIF<Key,​Value,​Wrapper>
    The storage manager cares for the storage of the cached data. This is more or less just a map to access values by the key. However when using a weak key storage the storage logic is slightly different therefore the storage manager is not part of the general cache logic but
